article.description: Mays gets 8th double-double; Bakersfield beats UTPA 66-54
article.headline: Mays gets 8th double-double; Bakersfield beats UTPA 66-54
article.linkText: Mays gets 8th double-double; Bakersfield beats UTPA 66-54
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Kevin Mays led a balanced Cal State Bakersfield attack with 14 points and 10 rebounds as the Roadrunners beat Texas-Pan American 66-54 on Thursday night. It was Mays' eighth double-double of the season. Aly Ahmed and Brent Wrapp had 13 points apiece for Bakersfield (10-15, 5-4 Western Athletic Conference) and Jaylin Airington added 10. It was a season-high for the freshman Wrapp, who also had five rebounds and seven assists. Javonte Maynor's 3-pointer capped a 17-4 stretch to open the game for Bakersfield. Ahmed's basket at the 5:41 mark gave them a 25-9 lead -- the Roadrunners' largest of the half -- but UTPA closed on a 12-6 run. Janari Joesaar hit 12 of 16 free throws and finished with 18 points for UTPA (8-17, 2-7). Shaquille Boga added 15 points and six assists. The Roadrunners had a 37-22 advantage on the glass, including 12-4 on the offensive end.
